.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-DIFF" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.51" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-diff \- Compare two tracked job submissions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose diff [OPTIONS] [JOB_ID_1] [JOB_ID_2]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Compare tracked submission metadata, effective config snapshots, selected resource settings, and observed outcomes between two jobs. With \-\-across <SWEEP_ID> or \-\-jobs <a,b,c> the comparison becomes an N\-way matrix (one column per run, one row per field that differs in at least one run).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fIJOB_ID_1\fR
Earlier or left\-hand tracked job id.
.TP
\fIJOB_ID_2\fR
Later or right\-hand tracked job id.
.TP
\fB--across\fR \fISWEEP_ID\fR
Compare every submitted trial of this sweep id as an N\-way matrix.
.TP
\fB--jobs\fR \fIJOB_IDS\fR
Compare these tracked job ids as an N\-way matrix (comma\-separated).
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Pairwise output format (text, json). Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--matrix\-format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
N\-way matrix output format (text, csv, json). Possible values: text, json, csv.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose diff 12345 12346 \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose diff 12345 12346 \-\-format json
hpc\-compose diff \-\-jobs 12345,12346,12347 \-\-matrix\-format json
hpc\-compose diff \-\-across sweep\-1700000000\-1234 \-\-matrix\-format csv
.fi
